.TH "bote" "1" "2019-05-13" "bote 1.0" "User Commands"
.P
.SH NAME
.RS 4
\fBbote\fR - a notetaking and note management utility written in fish
.RE
.SH SYNOPSIS
.RS 4
\fBbote\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR...] \fIOPERATION\fR [\fIARGUMENTS\fR...]
.RE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.RS 4
\fBbote\fR is a notetaking and note management utility written in the fish shell. It implements functionality for editing, removing, moving, organizing, backuping, and (re)arranging notes.
.P
By default, `~/notes` is used as the root directory for any and all notes.
By default, the logfile is located at `~/.botelog`.
By default, the stylesheet to be used when one isn't provded with \fB--stylesheet, -S\fR is `~/.md_css/tufte/tufte.css`.
.RE
.SH OPERATIONS
.RS 4
\fBbote\fR supports many different operations. Some require no additional arguments, while some require a fixed or variable amount of additional arguments.
.P
\fBcreate-category, C\fR
.br
	bote create-category \fICC\fR
.P
Create a new category using the supplied category chain.
.P
\fBremove-category, D\fR
.br
	bote remove-category \fICC\fR
.P
Remove the category specified in the category chain.
.P
\fBmove-category, M\fR
.br
	bote move-category \fICC\fR \fICC\fR
.P
Move a category from one category chain to another.
.P
\fBcreate, c\fR
.br
	bote create [\fICC\fR] \fInote_name\fR
.P
Create a note in the specified category chain or in the root category if one is not given.
.P
\fBremove, d\fR
.br
	bote remove [\fICC\fR] \fInote_name\fR
.P
Remove a note in the specified category chain or in the root category if one is not given.
.P
\fBmove, m\fR
.br
	bote move [\fICC\fR] \fInote_name\fR \fICC\fR
.P
Move a note from the specified category chain (or from the root category if one is not given) to another.
.P
\fBsanitize, s\fR
.br
	bote sanitize
.P
Sanitize the entire folder structure (make sure that every category chain has a 'pdf' directory inside of it)
.P
\fBlist, l\fR
.br
	bote list
.P
List the entire note tree.
.P
\fBbackup, b\fR
.br
	bote backup [\fI-z\fR] \fIPATH\fR
.P
Backup the entire note tree to the TAR archive specified by \fIPATH\fR.
.P
\fBrestore, r\fR
.br
	bote restore [\fI-z\fR] \fIPATH\fR
.P
Restore the note tree from the backup TAR archive specified by \fIPATH\fR to the current root directory. Notes that already exist in the "local" root tree are replaced only if they are older than their backup counterparts.
.P
\fBedit, e\fR
.br
	bote edit [\fICC\fR] [\fInote_name\fR]
.P
Start editing a note in the specified category chain. The note's markdown file is opened inside of \fBneovim\fR, and the associated PDF file is opened inside of "mupdf". Once \fBneovim\fR is closed, the associated \fBmupdf\fR process is terminated as well. On save, the markdown file's PDF counterpart is updated using \fBpandoc, wkhtmltopdf\fR and the specified CSS stylesheet, and the PDF view is updated.
.P
\fBview, v\fR
.br
	bote view [\fICC] [\fRnote_name_]
.P
View the note's PDF file.
.RE
.SH CATEGORY CHAINS (CC)
.RS 4
A \fBcategory chain\fR simply represents a "chain" of categories nested inside one another. Categories are separated using a slash (/).
.P
e.g. the category chain \fBlinux/drives/booting\fR could be read as: category \fBbooting\fR is a category that resides inside of the category \fBdrives\fR that resides inside of the category \fBlinux\fR, that resides in the root category
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.RS 4
\fB--help, -h\fR
.br
    	Display help and exit.
.P
\fB--root-directory\fR \fIPATH\fR, \fB-r\fR \fIPATH\fR
.br
    	Use an alternative \fBrootdir\fR for the following operation.
.P
\fB--stylesheet\fR \fIPATH\fR, \fB-S\fR \fIPATH\fR
.br
    	Use an alternative CSS stylesheet for the following operation.
.P
\fB--logfile\fR \fIPATH\fR, \fB-L\fR \fIPATH\fR
.br
		Use an alternative path for the logging file.
.P
\fB--gzip, -z\fR
.br
    	Specfiy that the TAR archive provided for the backup/restore operation is also gzipped.
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.RS 4
Some of the environment variables that \fBbote\fR uses.
.P
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.IP \(bu 4
.\}
\fBBOTE_ROOTDIR\fR: override the default root directory
.RE
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.IP \(bu 4
.\}
\fBBOTE_DEFAULTCSS\fR: override the default stylesheet
.RE
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.IP \(bu 4
.\}
\fBBOTE_LOGFILE\fR: override the path of the logfile
.RE
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.IP \(bu 4
.\}
\fBBOTE_EDITOR_CMDLINE\fR: a string which represents the commandline the shell will execute to start a text editor for editing markdown files, in which %f should serve as a placeholder for the filename (e.g. "nvim -c Goyo %f", "nano %f")
.br
	The value "vim %f" is used internally if the env. var is not set
.RE
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.IP \(bu 4
.\}
\fBBOTE_PDF_CMDLINE\fR: a string which represents the commandline the shell will execute to start a PDF reader for viewing PDF files, in which %f should serve as a placeholder for the PDF filename (e.g. "zathura %f", "mupdf %f")
.br
	The value "zathura %f" is used internally if the env. var is not set

.RE
.P
NOTE: Due to the current limitations of the fish shell, the environment variables \fBBOTE_PDF_CMDLINE\fR and \fBBOTE_EDITOR_CMDNLINE\fR may \fBnot\fR contain spaces inside of individual arguments. 
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS 4
bote c linux/testing stuff
.br
	Create a note named "stuff" in the category chain "linux/testing".
.P
bote d linux/testing stuff
.br
	Remove the note named "stuff" inside of the category chain "linux/testing.
.P
bote c stuff
.br
	Create a note named "stuff" in the root category.
.P
bote D linux/testing
.br
	Remove the category "testing" located in the "linux" category.
.P
bote b -z ~/noteback.tar.gz
.br
	Create a full, gzipped TAR backup of the root directory and store it at `~/noteback.tar.gz`
.P
bote r -z ~/noteback.tar.gz
.br
	Restore all the notes from the gzipped TAR backup located at `~/noteback.tar.gz`.
.P
bote e amazing
.br
	Begin editing a note called "amazing" located in the root category.
.P
bote m linux/stuff keep linux
.br
	Move the note called "keep" from the category chain "linux/stuff" to the category "linux". (like moving a file to the parent directory)
.P
bote M linux/stuff systems
.br
	Move the category "stuff" that is located in the "linux" category to the "systems" category. ("linux" and "systems" categoies are in the root category)
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.RS 4
\fBbote\fR should exit with exit status \fB0\fR if no errors occured, and with \fB1\fR otherwise.
.RE
